  "number": 333,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/333",
  "title": "Allow debouncing the image loading of the hits template",
  "body": "Following #302 and #307\n\nIt seems that in some situations we could allow users to debounce the image loading.\n\nOne solution:\n\nhits({container, lazyloadImages})\n\nOn the implementation side:\n\nUsers will have to use ais-src=real-src.jpg on images + src={helpers.lazySrc}\nWe listen to onload on main hits container\nIf onload element === img && img.ais-src => load the image in 100ms\nIf newsearch before 100ms, discard all previous images\nWe can use classes and shit to allow displaying images with fadein fadeout\nI think we should not try to lazyload for now (only load what's visible), this is a harder topic to include as an API\n",
